cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD 

This paper discusses the properties of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and word embeddings in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves hyperparameter search and proposes a novel class of recurrent-like neural networks, which falls under the categories of cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the geometric properties of RNNs, which could be related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SD (Systems and Control).
